14/01/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu said on Friday (January 11th) that he backs "without reservations" the NATO membership bids of Albania, Croatia, and Macedonia. 
Regarding the Alliance summit that Bucharest will host in early April, the president urged NATO to adopt a better approach towards Georgia and Ukraine. 
NATO should also establish closer ties with Serbia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Montenegro, Basescu said. 
NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer visited Bucharest on Friday to discuss preparations for the summit. 
(AP, Xinhua - 11/01/08)
